[5.95, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208mdata_description\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "Binary classification of DNA sequences (positives: human enhancers; negatives: random GRCh38 sequences). train.csv:\r\n123,872 rows, columns: sequence (string), id (int), numeric_label (0/1). Labels are perfectly balanced (61,936 per\r\nclass). Sequences are variable length: mean 269 bp, std 123, min 2, max 573. Length distribution roughly centered at 269\r\nwith IQR 177\u2013361; 90th percentile ~423. Base composition overall: A 28.0%, C 21.9%, G 21.9%, T 28.1%, N ~0.05%. Very few\r\nNs overall (17,581 total).\r\n"]
[0.0, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208mfeature_analysis\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "Label balance: 50/50. Length stats identical across labels (means ~269, same quantiles), suggesting negatives were\r\nlength-matched. N content: positives contain essentially no Ns; about 0.1% of negative sequences contain Ns (mean\r\nfraction 0.0011 for negatives, 0 for positives), so Ns are rare and not a major feature. Unique chars limited to\r\nA/C/G/T/N. No other metadata besides id.\r\n"]
[0.0, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208mdomain_insights\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "Data type: nucleotide sequences of moderate variable length (2\u2013573 bp), classical enhancer vs genomic background task.\r\nBalanced classes simplify metrics and loss weighting. Variable lengths but modest max length allow simple fixed-length\r\nencodings (e.g., truncate/pad to 573 or a chosen length). Ns are rare\u2014can map to zero vector. Domain: positives are\r\nknown enhancers (FANTOM5/Ensembl), negatives are random genomic regions length-matched and non-overlapping; potential\r\nreliance on k-mer composition. Challenges: slight presence of Ns mostly in negatives; otherwise clean. Opportunities:\r\nclassical baselines like k-mer counts with logistic regression/SVM are appropriate for iteration 0; bag-of-k-mers with\r\n4-mers/6-mers feasible. GPU not necessary for baseline; CPU fine for counting and linear models.\r\n"]
[0.0, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208mfiles_created\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "['eda.py', 'len_label.py', 'base_comp.py']\r\n"]
[0.061, "o", "\u001b[1;35mITERATION \u001b[0m\u001b[1;35m0\u001b[0m\u001b[1;35m | SPLITTING STEP\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[11.447, "o", "\u001b[96magent runs bash command\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[6.246, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208mtrain_path\u001b[0m\r\n/workspace/runs/yearning_weariness_watch/train.csv\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208mval_path\u001b[0m\r\n/workspace/runs/yearning_weariness_watch/validation.csv\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208msplitting_strategy\u001b[0m\r\nStratified 80/20 split on numeric_label using sklearn.model_selection.train_test_split (random_state=42, shuffle=True).\r\nEnsures both classes are proportionally represented in train and validation to mirror unseen data class balance.\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208mfiles_created\u001b[0m\r\n['train.csv', 'validation.csv']\r\n"]
[0.012, "o", "\u001b[1;35mITERATION \u001b[0m\u001b[1;35m0\u001b[0m\u001b[1;35m | REPRESENTATION STEP\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[8.489, "o", "\u001b[96magent writes python file\u001b[0m representation.py\r\n"]
[4.428, "o", "\u001b[96magent runs bash command\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[5.269, "o", "\u001b[96magent runs bash command\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.45, "o", "\u001b[96magent runs bash command\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.705, "o", "\u001b[96magent runs bash command\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.399, "o", "\u001b[96magent runs bash command\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.39, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208mrepresentation\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.0, "o", "Character k-mer bag-of-words. Using scikit-learn CountVectorizer with analyzer='char', fixed ngram_range=(6,6) (6-mers),\r\nlowercase=False to preserve A/C/G/T/N, min_df=1. Each sequence is transformed into a sparse count vector of all observed\r\n6-mers; Ns are treated as literal characters in k-mers. Saved artifacts: features as .npz, labels as joblib if present,\r\nand the fitted vectorizer as joblib. Script: representation.py with CLI to fit on train (\"--fit\") and transform other\r\nsplits using the saved vectorizer.\r\n"]
[0.0, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208mfiles_created\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.0, "o", "['representation.py']\r\n"]
[0.053, "o", "\u001b[1;35mITERATION \u001b[0m\u001b[1;35m0\u001b[0m\u001b[1;35m | ARCHITECTURE STEP\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[8.634, "o", "\u001b[96magent writes python file\u001b[0m model_train.py\r\n"]
[2.31, "o", "\u001b[96magent runs python file\u001b[0m model_train.py\r\n"]
[58.087, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208marchitecture\u001b[0m\r\nLinear model (logistic regression) on 6-mer character bag-of-words. Features: CountVectorizer(analyzer='char',\r\nngram_range=(6,6), lowercase=False)."]
[0.001, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208mhyperparameters\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.0, "o", "penalty=l2, C=1.0, solver=saga, max_iter=200, n_jobs=-1, val_split=0.2 stratified with random_state=42.\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208mfiles_created\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.0, "o", "['model_train.py', 'logreg_model.joblib', 'vectorizer.joblib']\r\n"]
[0.04, "o", "\u001b[1;35mITERATION \u001b[0m\u001b[1;35m0\u001b[0m\u001b[1;35m | TRAINING STEP\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.975, "o", "\u001b[96magent runs bash command\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[16.348, "o", "\u001b[96magent writes python file\u001b[0m train.py\r\n"]
[1.861, "o", "\u001b[96magent runs python file\u001b[0m train.py\r\n"]
[42.68, "o", "TRAINING REPRODUCIBILITY OK\r\n"]
[0.003, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208mpath_to_train_file\u001b[0m\r\n/workspace/runs/yearning_weariness_watch/train.py\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208mpath_to_model_file\u001b[0m\r\n/workspace/runs/yearning_weariness_watch/training_artifacts/model.joblib\r\n"]
[0.0, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208mpath_to_artifacts_dir\u001b[0m\r\n/workspace/runs/yearning_weariness_watch/training_artifacts\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208mtraining_summary\u001b[0m\r\nImplemented a baseline character 6-mer bag-of-words representation with a linear SGDClassifier (logistic loss). Train.py\r\nloads CSVs, fits CountVectorizer on 6-mers, trains with partial_fit across epochs with early stopping on validation log\r\nloss, and saves the best checkpoint plus vectorizer and metadata.\r\n"]
[0.0, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208munresolved_issues\u001b[0m\r\nNone\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208mfiles_created\u001b[0m\r\n['training_artifacts', 'train.py']\r\n"]
[0.023, "o", "\u001b[1;35mITERATION \u001b[0m\u001b[1;35m0\u001b[0m\u001b[1;35m | INFERENCE STEP\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.257, "o", "\u001b[96magent runs bash command\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.584, "o", "\u001b[96magent runs bash command\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[5.446, "o", "\u001b[96magent writes python file\u001b[0m inference.py\r\n"]
[2.406, "o", "\u001b[96magent edits file\u001b[0m inference.py\r\n"]
[1.977, "o", "\u001b[96magent runs bash command\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[16.44, "o", "\u001b[1;34mRUNNING DRY RUN EVAL\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.314, "o", "DRY RUN EVAL SUCCESS\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208mpath_to_inference_file\u001b[0m\r\n/workspace/runs/yearning_weariness_watch/inference.py\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208minference_summary\u001b[0m\r\nImplements inference for the baseline 6-mer CountVectorizer + SGDClassifier model. Loads vectorizer and model from the\r\nartifacts directory, transforms sequences, computes predict_proba, outputs id, predicted class, and class probabilities\r\nto CSV.\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208munresolved_issues\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.0, "o", "None\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208mfiles_created\u001b[0m\r\n['dry_run_metrics.txt', 'inference.py']\r\n"]
[0.026, "o", "\u001b[1;35mITERATION \u001b[0m\u001b[1;35m0\u001b[0m\u001b[1;35m | PREDICTION EXPLORATION STEP\u001b[0m\r\n"]
