[7.105, "o", "\u001b[96magent runs bash command\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[19.053, "o", "\u001b[96magent writes python file\u001b[0m analyze_val.py\r\n"]
[1.408, "o", "\u001b[96magent runs python file\u001b[0m analyze_val.py\r\n"]
[19.19, "o", "\u001b[1;34mRUNNING DRY RUN EVAL\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.462, "o", "DRY RUN EVAL SUCCESS\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208mstatistics\u001b[0m\r\nValidation set (stratified 20% holdout): accuracy 0.7866, balanced_accuracy 0.7866, ROC-AUC 0.8627, log_loss 0.4862,\r\nprecision 0.8056, recall 0.7556, F1 0.7798. Confusion matrix [[TN 10129, FP 2259],[FN 3027, TP 9360]].\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208minsights\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "Model is moderately calibrated (mean prob positive: true0=0.254, true1=0.703) but shows confidence extremes: many FPs\r\nwith prob>0.99 and FNs with prob\u22480. Probability thresholds at 0.5 yield slightly higher precision than recall, so the\r\nclassifier is conservative on positives. Errors are not strongly length-dependent; accuracy per length quartile ranges\r\n0.77\u20130.80. Ns are rare and likely not driving errors. High-confidence mistakes suggest some k-mer patterns strongly\r\nmislead the linear model (both directions), indicating overconfident weights on certain 6-mers.\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;208mfiles_created\u001b[0m\r\n['analyze_val.py', 'dry_run_metrics.txt', 'val_preds.csv']\r\n"]
[0.106, "o", "Starting evaluation phase\r\n  Running validation inference...\r\n"]
